properties.label: Agave fibres nes
properties.description: Including inter alia: Haiti hemp (Agave foetida); henequen (A. fourcroydes); ixtle, tampico (A. lecheguilla); maguey (A. cantala); pita (A. americana); Salvador hemp (A. letonae). See 789. The leaves of some agave varieties are used for the production of alcoholic beverages, such as aquamiel, mezcal, pulque and tequila.

properties.label: Alcohol non food
properties.description: Includes undenatured ethyl alcohol (strength by volume of > 80%) and denatured (any strength).

properties.label: Alfalfa meal and pellets
properties.description: Alfalfa (lucerne) dried, whole, cut, chopped, milled, pressed or pelletized.

properties.label: Almonds shelled
properties.description: Around 55% of the weight in shell.

properties.label: Almonds, with shell
properties.description: Prunus amygdalus; P. communis; Amygdalus communis. Produced mainly in Mediterranean countries, the United States and Asia.

properties.label: Animals live nes
properties.description: Any other animal grown for meat, eggs, feathers and skins, e.g. ostrich, antelope, deer, reindeer, chamois.

properties.label: Anise, badian, fennel, coriander
properties.description: Include: anise (Pimpinella anisum); badian or star anise (Illicium verum); caraway (Carum carvi); coriander (Coriandrum sativum); cumin (Cuminum cyminum); fennel (Foeniculum vulgare); juniper berries (Juniperus communis). Seeds and berries from the various plants listed. They are normally used as spices, but also have industrial (e.g. in distilleries) and medicinal applications.

properties.label: Apples
properties.description: Malus pumila; M. sylvestris; M. communis; Pyrus malus.

properties.label: Apricots
properties.description: Prunus armeniaca.

properties.label: Apricots, dry
properties.description: Prepared either by direct drying in the sun or by industrial processes. May be marketed as slices or blocks of pulp, either dried or evaporated.

properties.label: Areca nuts
properties.description: Areca, betel nut (Areca catechu). Produced mainly in the Far East. Areca nuts are used mainly as masticatory. These nuts contain alkaloids (arecoline and arecaidine).

properties.label: Artichokes
properties.description: Cynara scolymus.

properties.label: Artificial sweeteners
properties.description: High-intensity or low-caloric sweetening agents that are produced chemically.

properties.label: Asparagus
properties.description: Asparagus officinalis.

properties.label: Asses
properties.description: Equus asinus. See 866.

properties.label: Avocados
properties.description: Persea americana.

properties.label: Bacon and ham
properties.description: Meat of pigs, whether salted, in brine, dried or smoked.

properties.label: Bagasse
properties.description: Residue consisting of the fibrous portion of the sugar cane after the juice has been extracted. Used as a fuel in sugar mills, as an animal feed, and in paper production.

properties.label: Bambara beans
properties.description: Bambara groundnut, earth pea (Voandzeia subterranea). These beand are grown underground in a similar way to groundnuts.

properties.label: Bananas
properties.description: Musa sapientum; M. cavendishii; M. nana. Bananas are normally eaten raw. Trade figures may include dried bananas. Data should be reported excluding the weight of the central stalk.

properties.label: Barley
properties.description: Hordeum spp.: two-row barley (H. disticum) six-row barley (H. hexasticum) four-row barley (H. vulgare). Tolerates poorer soils and lower temperatures better than does wheat. Varieties include with husk and without (naked). Used as a livestock feed, for malt and for preparing foods. The roasted grains are a coffee substitute.

properties.label: Barley, pearled
properties.description: Small, round pellets obtained by the further milling of pot barley. This definition also includes kibbled, rolled or flaked grains.

properties.label: Barley, pot
properties.description: Whole-seed barley with the husks, hulls and bran removed.

properties.label: Bastfibres, other
properties.description: Including inter alia: China jute (Abutilon avicennae); Congo jute, malva, paka (Urena lobata; U. sinuata); Indian flax (Abroma augusta); kenaf, meshta (Hibiscus cannabinus); rosella hemp (H. sabdariffa); sunn hemp (Crotalaria juncea). This definition covers all textile fibres extracted from the stems of dicotyledonous plants, o/t flax, ramie, true hemp and true jute. For trade coverage see 780.

properties.label: Beans, dry
properties.description: Phaseolus spp.: kidney, haricot bean (Ph. vulgaris); lima, butter bean (Ph. lunatus); adzuki bean (Ph. angularis); mungo bean, golden, green gram (Ph. aureus); black gram, urd (Ph. mungo); scarlet runner bean (Ph. coccineus); rice bean (Ph. calcaratus); moth bean (Ph. aconitifolius); tepary bean (Ph. acutifolius). Only species of Phaseolus should be included, though several countries also include certain types of beans. Commonly classified as Vigna (angularis, mungo, radiata, aconitifolia). In the past, these species were also classified as Phaseolus.

properties.label: Beans, green
properties.description: Phaseolus and Vigna spp.. For shelling.

properties.label: Beehives
properties.description: Apis mellifica; A. dorsata; A. florea; A. indica. A beehive is an artificial habitation for bees.

properties.label: Beer of barley
properties.description: Beverage that may be alcoholic or non-alcoholic that is made from fermented malted cereals (mainly barley), water and hops. Non-malted cereals may also be used. The FAO definition differs from the main international classifications in that it includes non-alcoholic beer.

properties.label: Beer of maize
properties.description: Prepared either from malted or unmalted cereal.

properties.label: Beer of millet
properties.description: A traditional beer prepared in African countries in which millets are cultivated. It is normally consumed while still fermenting.

properties.label: Beer of sorghum
properties.description: A traditional beer prepared in African countries in which sorghum is cultivated. It is normally consumed while still fermenting.

properties.label: Beeswax
properties.description: The substance bees use to build the hexagonal cells of the combs of beehives. Includes other insect waxes as well, i.e. lac and Chinese wax.

properties.label: Beet pulp
properties.description: Residue from the extraction of sugar from the root of sugar beets. Used for animal feed.

properties.label: Beet tops
properties.description: Beet tops, consisting of the leaves and upper part of the root, are used for feed. They account for about 25% of plant weight, though it is uncertain how much, if any, of this is included in national production statistics.

properties.label: Beets for fodder
properties.description: Beet, beetroot, mangold (Beta vulgaris). Especially cultivated for fodder.

properties.label: Berries nes
properties.description: Including inter alia: blackberry (Morus nigra); loganberry; white, red mulberry (M. alba; M. rubra); myrtle berry (Myrtus communis) huckleberry, dangleberry (Gaylussacia spp.). Other berries not separately identified. In some countries, some or all of the berries listed previously are reported under this general category.

properties.label: Beverages, distilled alcoholic
properties.description: Includes undenatured ethyl alcohol (strength by volume < 80%); spirits, liqueurs and other spirituous beverages and preparations.

properties.label: Beverages, fermented rice
properties.description: Low-alcohol beverages, such as rice wine and sake.

properties.label: Beverages, fermented wheat
properties.description: Low-alcohol beverages from fermented flour, e.g. Korean jakju and takju.

properties.label: Beverages, non alcoholic
properties.description: Includes sweetened or flavoured mineral waters and other non-alcoholic beverages, such as lemonade, orangeade, cola, etc. Excludes fruit and vegetable juices.

properties.label: Blueberries
properties.description: European blueberry, wild bilberry, whortleberry (Vaccinium myrtillus); American blueberry (V. corymbosum). Trade data may include cranberries, myrtle berries and other fruits of the genus Vaccinium.

properties.label: Bran, barley
properties.description: A by-product of the production of pot barley.

properties.label: Bran, buckwheat
properties.description: A milling by-product.

properties.label: Bran, cereals nes
properties.description: A milling by-product.

properties.label: Bran, fonio
properties.description: A milling by-product.

properties.label: Bran, maize
properties.description: A by-product of the milling of shelled maize.

properties.label: Bran, millet
properties.description: A milling by-product.

properties.label: Bran, mixed grains
properties.description: A milling by-product.

properties.label: Bran, oats
properties.description: By-product of milling oats for human consumption, containing mainly hulls and fragments of the endosperm (oat millfeed), as well as residues from hulling, rolling, flaking, etc.

properties.label: Bran, pulses
properties.description: Bran, sharps and other residues from the milling or working of pulses.

properties.label: Bran, rice
properties.description: A by-product of polishing brown rice, comprising the pericarp, aleurone layer, embryo and some endosperm.

properties.label: Bran, rye
properties.description: A milling by-product.

properties.label: Bran, sorghum
properties.description: A milling by-product.

properties.label: Bran, triticale
properties.description: A milling by-product.

properties.label: Bran, wheat
properties.description: Defined broadly to include sharps and other residue from the milling, sifting or other working of the grain. Contains a little flour.

properties.label: Brazil nuts, shelled
properties.description: Around 55% of the weight in shell.

properties.label: Brazil nuts, with shell
properties.description: Brazil, Para or cream nut (Bertholletia excelsa).

properties.label: Bread
properties.description: A baked product of flour or meal of cereals, especially wheat. Includes ordinary, unleavened, crackers, rusks, etc.

properties.label: Broad beans, horse beans, dry
properties.description: Vicia faba: horse-bean (var. equina); broad bean (var. major); field bean (var. minor).

properties.label: Buckwheat
properties.description: Fagopyrum esculentum (Polygonaceae). A minor cereal cultivated primarily in northern regions. Buckwheat is considered a cereal, although it does not belong to the gramineous family.

properties.label: Buffaloes
properties.description: Indian, Asiatic, pigmy, water buffalo (Bubalus bubalus; B. arnee; B. depressicornis); African buffalo (genus Syncerus); American bison (Bison bison); European bison (Bison bonasus); beeffalo (cross between a bison and a domesticated beef animal). See 866. Excludes wild bisons and buffaloes.

properties.label: Bulgur
properties.description: Whole wheat grains that are boiled, dried and cracked, either between stones or in a hand mill. Very popular in the Near East.

properties.label: Butter of karite nuts
properties.description: A very important vegetable oil in West Africa. Used as a substitute for cocoa butter and in cosmetics.

properties.label: Butter, cow milk
properties.description: Emulsion of milk fat and water that is obtained by churning cream. Trade data cover butter from the milk of any animal.

properties.label: Buttermilk, curdled, acidified milk
properties.description: Residue from butter making. Includes kephir.

properties.label: Cabbage for fodder
properties.description: Brassica chinensis; B. oleracea. Especially cultivated for fodder.

properties.label: Cabbages and other brassicas
properties.description: Chinese, mustard cabbage, pak-choi (Brassica chinensis); white, red, savoy cabbage, Brussels sprouts, collards, kale and kohlrabi (Brassica oleracea all var. except botrytis).

properties.label: Cake, copra
properties.description: Residue from oil extraction.

properties.label: Cake, cottonseed
properties.description: Residue from oil extraction.

properties.label: Cake, groundnuts
properties.description: Residue from oil extraction.

properties.label: Cake, hempseed
properties.description: Residue from oil extraction.

properties.label: Cake, kapok
properties.description: Residue from oil extraction.

properties.label: Cake, linseed
properties.description: Residue from oil extraction.

properties.label: Cake, maize
properties.description: A residue of the extraction of oil from germ.

properties.label: Cake, mustard
properties.description: Residue from oil extraction.

properties.label: Cake, oilseeds nes
properties.description: Residue from oil extraction.

properties.label: Cake, palm kernel
properties.description: Residue from oil extraction.

properties.label: Cake, poppy seed
properties.description: Residue from oil extraction.

properties.label: Cake, rapeseed
properties.description: Residue from oil extraction.

properties.label: Cake, rice bran
properties.description: A residue of the extraction of oil. Also known as de-oiled rice bran.

properties.label: Cake, safflower
properties.description: Residue from oil extraction.

properties.label: Cake, sesame seed
properties.description: Residue from oil extraction.

properties.label: Cake, soybeans
properties.description: Oilcake and other solid residues (except dregs), whether or not ground, or in the form of pellets, resulting from the extraction of fats or oils.

properties.label: Cake, sunflower
properties.description: Residue from oil extraction. The cake is used for feed if it is from decorticated seeds, or for fertilizer if it comes from undecorticated seeds.

properties.label: Camelids, other
properties.description: Various species of Lama: e.g. glama pacos (alpaca); peruana (llama); huanacos (guanaco>); vicugna (vicuÂ¤a). See 866.

properties.label: Camels
properties.description: Bactrian camel (Camelus bactrianus); Arabian camel (C. dromedarius). See 866.

properties.label: Canary seed
properties.description: Phalaris canariensis. Minor cereal normally used as bird feed.

properties.label: Cane tops
properties.description: The leaves and upper part of the stalks, which are used for feed. The tops represent about 10% of the weight of the plant.

properties.label: Carobs
properties.description: Ceratonia siliqua Carob-tree, locust bean. Includes also seeds. Mainly used as an animal feed and for industrial purposes. Rich in pectin.

properties.label: Carrots and turnips
properties.description: Daucus carota. Trade data may include turnips (Brassica rapa var. rapifera).

properties.label: Carrots for fodder
properties.description: Daucus carota. Especially cultivated for fodder.

properties.label: Casein
properties.description: The main protein constituent of milk. Casein is obtained from skimmed milk by precipitation (curdling) with acids or rennet.

properties.label: Cashew nuts, shelled
properties.description: Around 25% of the weight in shell.

properties.label: Cashew nuts, with shell
properties.description: Anacardium occidentale. Produced mainly in East Africa, India and Brazil.

properties.label: Cashewapple
properties.description: Anacardium occidentale. The thickened, fleshy stem below the cashew nut. When soft it is used for jam.

properties.label: Cassava
properties.description: Manioc, mandioca, yuca (Manihot esculenta, syn. M. utilissima); yuca dulce (M. palmata, syn. M. dulcis). A semi-permanent crop grown in tropical and subtropical regions. Sometimes bitter and sweet cassavas are referred to as separate species, the former being M. esculenta and the latter M. palmata, but this is incorrect since the toxicity varies according to location. Cassava is the staple food in many tropical countries. It is not traded internationally in its fresh state because tubers deteriorate very rapidly.

properties.label: Cassava dried
properties.description: Includes peeled, sliced and sun-dried (cassava chips), as well as ground and compressed cassava (pellets). Used mainly as livestock feed.

properties.label: Cassava leaves
properties.description: Manihot esculenta; M. utilissima. Young cassava leaves are eaten in some areas of Africa as a vegetable.

properties.label: Castor oil seed
properties.description: Ricinus communis. Valued mainly for their oil, which is used in pharmaceutical products. Ground seedcakes are used as fertilizers (castor oil pomace).

properties.label: Castor oil, hydrogenated (opal wax)
properties.description: Also called "opal wax".

properties.label: Cattle
properties.description: Common ox (Bos taurus); zebu, humped ox (Bos indicus); Asiatic ox (subgenus Bibos); Tibetan yak (Poephagus grunniens). Animals of the genus listed, regardless of age, sex, or purpose raised. Data are expressed in number of heads.

properties.label: Cauliflowers and broccoli
properties.description: Brassica oleracea var. botrytis, subvariety cauliflora and cymosa. Includes headed broccoli.

properties.label: Cereal preparations, nes
properties.description: Cereal grains, excluding barley and oats, that are either rolled, flaked, pearled, sliced or kibbled.

properties.label: Cereals, breakfast
properties.description: Foods prepared by swelling and roasting cereals or cereal products, e.g. corn flakes, puffed rice; cereals o/t maize, in grain form, precooked or otherwise prepared.

properties.label: Cereals, nes
properties.description: Including inter alia: canagua or coaihua (Chenopodium pallidicaule); quihuicha or Inca wheat (Amaranthus caudatus); adlay or Job's tears (Coix lacryma-jobi); wild rice (Zizania aquatica). Other cereal crops that are not identified separately because of their minor relevance at the international level. Because of their limited local importance, some countries report cereals under this commodity heading that are classified individually by FAO.

properties.label: Cheese, skimmed cow milk
properties.description: May include some whole milk.

properties.label: Cheese, whole cow milk
properties.description: Curd of milk that has been coagulated and separated from whey. May include some skimmed milk.

properties.label: Cherries
properties.description: Mazzard, sweet cherry (Prunus avium; Cerasus avium); hard-fleshed cherry (var. duracina); heart cherry (var. juliana).

properties.label: Cherries, sour
properties.description: Prunus cerasus; Cerasus acida.

properties.label: Chestnut
properties.description: Castanea spp.: C. vesca; C. vulgaris; C. sativa. Produced mainly in Europe and Asia.

properties.label: Chick peas
properties.description: Chickpea, Bengal gram, garbanzos (Cicer arietinum).

properties.label: Chickens
properties.description: Fowl (Gallus domesticus); Guinea fowl (Numida meleagris. Domesticated birds only. Data are expressed in thousands.

properties.label: Chicory roots
properties.description: Horium intybus; C. sativum. Unroasted chicory roots.

properties.label: Chillies and peppers, dry
properties.description: Red and cayenne pepper, paprika, chillies (Capsicum frutescens; C. annuum); allspice, Jamaica pepper (Pimenta officinalis). Uncrushed or unground fresh pimentos are considered to be vegetables.

properties.label: Chillies and peppers, green
properties.description: Capsicum annuum; C. fructescens; Pimenta officinalis. Production data exclude crops cultivated explicitly as spices. In contrast, trade data include these crops, provided they are fresh, uncrushed and unground.

properties.label: Chocolate products nes
properties.description: Includes sweetened cocoa powder, chocolate and other food preparations containing cocoa, as well as sugar confectionery containing cocoa in any amount. Excludes white chocolate (see 168).

properties.label: Cider etc
properties.description: Fermented beverages nes (e.g. cider, perry, mead), including alcoholic beverages (that are not distilled) made from cereals, roots and fruits, that are not included under other headings, e.g. beer from plantains and ginger.

properties.label: Cigarettes
properties.description: Includes cigarettes of tobacco substitutes.

properties.label: Cigars, cheroots
properties.description: Includes cigars, cheroots and cigarillos of tobacco substitutes.

properties.label: Cinnamon (canella)
properties.description: Ceylon cinnamon (Cinnamomum zeylanicum); Chinese, common cinnamon, cassia (C. cassia). The inner bark of young branches of certain trees of the Laurus family. Includes cinnamon- tree flowers, cinnamon fruit and cinnamon waste (chips), whether whole, crushed or ground.

properties.label: Cloves
properties.description: Eugenia caryophyllata; Caryophyllus aromaticus. The whole fruit of the clove tree, including the flowers picked before maturity and dried in the sun, and the stems of the clove flowers.

properties.label: Cocoa, beans
properties.description: Theobroma cacao. The seeds contained in the fruit of the cacao- tree, including whole or broken, raw or roasted.

properties.label: Cocoa, butter
properties.description: Obtained by hot-pressing either cocoa paste or the whole bean. Includes the fat and oil.

properties.label: Cocoa, husks, shell
properties.description: Including skins and other cocoa waste.

properties.label: Cocoa, paste
properties.description: Obtained by grinding roasted cocoa beans. Also called liquor. Not defatted.

properties.label: Cocoa, powder & cake
properties.description: Wholly or partly defatted paste (cake) and cake reduced to powder, without added sugar or other sweeteners.

properties.label: Coconuts
properties.description: Cocos nucifera Husked coconut. In shell, covered by the endocarp, while exocarp (the smooth outer skin) and mesocarp (the fibrous covering) are removed. Immature nuts contain a milky juice that is consumed as a refreshing drink. Mature nuts are consumed as such, or processed for copra or desiccated coconut. The flesh, from which copra/oil is extracted, constitutes 40-70% of the weight of the husked coconut. The oil content is about 36% of the flesh.

properties.label: Coconuts, desiccated
properties.description: Dried, shredded flesh of coconut processed for human consumption. It retains most of the oil and proteins of the fresh nut and is mainly used in confectionery and baking.

properties.label: Cocoons, unreelable & waste
properties.description: Include cocoons unsuitable for reeling and silk waste of all kinds. Not carded or combed.

properties.label: Coffee, extracts
properties.description: Essences and concentrates, including instant coffee, roasted chicory and other coffee substitutes, extracts and essences thereof.

properties.label: Coffee, green
properties.description: Coffea spp. (arabica, robusta, liberica). Raw coffee in all forms.

properties.label: Coffee, roasted
properties.description: With or without caffeine, and whether or not ground.

properties.label: Coffee, substitutes containing coffee
properties.description: Coffee substitutes containing coffee in any proportion.

properties.label: Coir
properties.description: Cocos nucifera. Coir fibre is obtained from the fibrous covering of the mesocarp. For trade coverage see 789.

properties.label: Copra
properties.description: The dried flesh of coconut from which the oil is extracted.

properties.label: Cotton lint
properties.description: Gossypium spp. Fibres from ginning seed cotton that have not been carded or combed. Trade data also include fibres that have been cleaned, bleached, dyed or rendered absorbent.

properties.label: Cotton linter
properties.description: Very short fibres that cover the seeds after ginning and that are very high in cellulose.

properties.label: Cotton waste
properties.description: Waste is produced when cotton is prepared for spinning, or during spinning operations, weaving, knitting, etc., or from garnetting cotton goods.

properties.label: Cotton, carded, combed
properties.description: Cotton (including garnetted stock and other cotton waste) which has been carded or combed, whether or not further prepared for spinning. May be bleached or dyed.

properties.label: Cottonseed
properties.description: Used for extracting oil.

properties.label: Cow peas, dry
properties.description: Cowpea, blackeye pea/bean (Vigna sinensis; Dolichos sinensis).

properties.label: Cranberries
properties.description: American cranberry (Vaccinium macrocarpon); European cranberry (V. oxycoccus). Trade data may include blueberries, myrtle berries and other fruits of the genus Vaccinium.

properties.label: Cream fresh
properties.description: That portion of milk which is rich in milk fat and is separated by skimming or centrifuging.

properties.label: Crude materials
properties.description: Trade data are expressed in value terms only. Including, of vegetable origin: bulbs, tubers, tuberous roots, corms, crowns and rhizomes; live plants, cuttings and slips; mushroom spawn; cut flowers and flower buds; foliage, branches and grasses, mosses and lichens; plants and parts used primarily in perfumes, pharmaceuticals, insecticides, fungicides, or for similar purposes; seaweeds and other algae; vegetable saps and extracts; materials used for plaiting, stuffing or padding; materials used primarily in brooms or brushes; and materials used primarily in dyeing and tanning. Includes of animal origin: human hair, unworked and waste; pigs bristles and hair; badger hair and other brush- making hair and waste; guts, bladders and stomachs of animals (o/t fish); skins and other parts of birds with their feathers or down; bones and horn-cores, unworked, defatted, simply prepared; powder and waste; ivory, tortoiseshell, whalebone, claws and beaks; coral and shells of molluscs and crustaceans; sponges of animal origin, ambergris, castoreum, civet and musk; cantharides, bile glands and other animal products used in pharmaceuticals.

properties.label: Cucumbers and gherkins
properties.description: Cucumis sativus.

properties.label: Currants
properties.description: Black (Ribes nigrum); red and white (R. rubrum). Trade data may sometimes include gooseberries.

properties.label: Dates
properties.description: Phoenix dactylifera. Includes fresh and dried fruit.

properties.label: Degras
properties.description: A residue from tanning leather that is obtained either by pressing or by extraction with solvents.

properties.label: Ducks
properties.description: Anas spp.. See 1057.

properties.label: Egg albumine
properties.description: The main protein constituent of egg white.

properties.label: Eggplants (aubergines)
properties.description: Solanum melongena. Also called aubergines.

properties.label: Eggs, dried
properties.description: Whole eggs and egg yolks, dried or powdered.

properties.label: Eggs, hen, in shell
properties.description: Weight in shell.

properties.label: Eggs, liquid
properties.description: Whole eggs, not in the shell, and egg yolks in liquid form that are frozen or otherwise preserved.

properties.label: Eggs, other bird, in shell
properties.description: Weight in shell.

properties.label: Fat, buffaloes
properties.description: See 869.

properties.label: Fat, camels
properties.description: Unrendered slaughter fats.

properties.label: Fat, cattle
properties.description: Unrendered slaughter fats from bovine animals, including edible and inedible fats that are removed in the course of dressing the carcass.

properties.label: Fat, cattle butcher
properties.description: Unrendered fats that are removed during butchering.

properties.label: Fat, goats
properties.description: Unrendered slaughter fats of goats. See 869.

properties.label: Fat, liver prepared (foie gras)
properties.description: Fatty livers of ducks and geese when cooked, prepared or preserved(e.g. patâ).

properties.label: Fat, nes, prepared
properties.description: Cooking fats prepared from both vegetable and animal oils and fats. Usually containing 100% fat.

properties.label: Fat, other camelids
properties.description: Unrendered slaughter fats.

properties.label: Fat, pig butcher
properties.description: See 871.

properties.label: Fat, pigs
properties.description: Unrendered slaughter fats of pigs. See 869.

properties.label: Fat, poultry
properties.description: Unrendered poultry fat.

properties.label: Fat, poultry, rendered
properties.description: Rendered poultry fat, including bone fat and fat obtained from waste.

properties.label: Fat, sheep
properties.description: Unrendered slaughter fats of sheep. See 869.

properties.label: Fatty acids
properties.description: Manufactured by the saponification or hydrolysis of natural fats or oils. Including acid oils from refining.

properties.label: Fatty substance residues
properties.description: Residues resulting from the treatment of fatty substances or animal or vegetable waxes.

properties.label: Feed additives
properties.description: See 851.

properties.label: Feed and meal, gluten
properties.description: Generally, by-products of the wet milling of maize. Gluten feed consists of fibres, spent germ and steep liquor. Gluten meal contains endosperm protein fractions that remain following starch recovery.

properties.label: Feed minerals
properties.description: See 851.

properties.label: Feed supplements
properties.description: Prepared animal feed that supplements the basic farm produced feed with organic or inorganic substances.

properties.label: Feed yeast
properties.description: Inactive dried yeast.

properties.label: Feed, compound, cattle
properties.description: Prepared animal feed designed to provide a balanced diet (complete feed).

properties.label: Feed, compound, nes
properties.description: See 840. See general note in the introduction.

properties.label: Feed, compound, pigs
properties.description: See 840.

properties.label: Feed, compound, poultry
properties.description: See 840.

properties.label: Feed, food waste preparations
properties.description: Same coverage as 653.

properties.label: Feed, other concentrates nes
properties.description: See 851.

properties.label: Feed, pulp of fruit
properties.description: Waste of fruit, fruit pomace and marc, excluding marc of grapes.

properties.label: Feed, vegetable products nes
properties.description: Vegetable products, vegetable waste, residues and by-products from the industrial processing of vegetable materials.

properties.label: Fibre crops nes
properties.description: Including inter alia: alfa, esparto (Lygeum spartum; Stipa tenacissima); bowstring hemp (Sansevieria spp.); caroa (Neoglaziovia variegata); fuque fibre (Furcraea macrophylla); Mauritius hemp (F. gigantea); New Zealand flax (Phormium tenax); palma ixtle (Samuela carnerosana). Other fibres that are not identified separately because of their minor relevance at the international level. Because of their limited local importance, some countries report vegetable fibres under this commodity heading that are classified individually by FAO. The fibre is obtained from the leaves, stalks or fruit of the plant. In instances where the fibrous part is normally used for other purposes, data cover only those fibres intended for spinning. For trade coverage see 789.

properties.label: Figs
properties.description: Ficus carica.

properties.label: Figs dried
properties.description: See 527.

properties.label: Flax fibre and tow
properties.description: Broken, scutched, hackled etc. but not spun. Traditionally, FAO has used this commodity to identify production in its raw state; in reality, the primary agricultural product is the commodity 771, which can either be used for the production of fibre or for other purposes.

properties.label: Flax fibre raw
properties.description: Linum usitatissimum Flax Straw. Flax is cultivated for seed as well as for fibre. The fibre is obtained from the stem of the plant. Data are reported in terms of straw.

properties.label: Flax tow waste
properties.description: Includes yarn waste and garnetted stock.

properties.label: Flour, barley and grits
properties.description: Fine flour and course meal obtained as milling by-products of pearled barley.

properties.label: Flour, buckwheat
properties.description: Broadly defined to include meal, groats and pellets. The flour is normally used in bread and crackers, and is also mixed with wheat flour. Meal and groats are normally used for soups.

properties.label: Flour, cassava
properties.description: A product of tubers that have been peeled, dried and milled; mainly for human consumption. Includes flour, meal and flakes.

properties.label: Flour, cereals
properties.description: Broadly defined to include meal, groats and pellets.

properties.label: Flour, fonio
properties.description: Broadly defined to include meal, groats and pellets.

properties.label: Flour, fruit
properties.description: Includes the flour, meal, powder, nuts and peel of fruits.

properties.label: Flour, maize
properties.description: Broadly defined to include meal, groats and pellets.

properties.label: Flour, millet
properties.description: Broadly defined to include meal, groats and pellets.

properties.label: Flour, mixed grain
properties.description: Broadly defined to include meal, groats and pellets.

properties.label: Flour, mustard
properties.description: Includes flour, meal and prepared mustard.

properties.label: Flour, oilseeds
properties.description: Flours and meals of oilseeds and oleaginous fruits (excluding mustard), non defatted or partially defatted.

properties.label: Flour, potatoes
properties.description: Produced from tubers that have been peeled, dried and milled. Includes flour, meal, flakes, granules and pellets.

properties.label: Flour, pulses
properties.description: Produced through milling or grinding of pulses. This heading also includes meal.

properties.label: Flour, rice
properties.description: Produced by milling broken or milled rice. Finely ground rice flour is widely used in infant foods and in noodles. It is not used in bread because it lacks the necessary gluten-forming protein.

properties.label: Flour, roots and tubers nes
properties.description: Flour and meal produced from roots and tubers o/t potatoes and cassava.

properties.label: Flour, rye
properties.description: Broadly defined to include meal, groats and pellets. In northern countries, rye flour is used primarily in bread.

properties.label: Flour, sorghum
properties.description: Broadly defined to include meal, groats and pellets.

properties.label: Flour, triticale
properties.description: Broadly defined to include meal, groats and pellets.

properties.label: Flour, wheat
properties.description: Defined broadly to include meal, groats and pellets. Strong flours from hard wheat are used for bread, while durum wheat flour is used primarily for pasta. Weaker flours from soft wheat are mainly used in cakes, pastries, biscuits and certain noodles.

properties.label: Fonio
properties.description: Digitaria spp.: fonio or findi (D. exilis); black fonio or hungry rice (D. iburua). A minor cereal of importance only in West Africa where it is eaten in place of rice during famines. The seeds are cooked by steaming the whole grain.

properties.label: Food prep nes
properties.description: Including both crop and livestock products. Inter alia: homogenized composite food preparations; soups and broths; ketchup and other sauces; mixed condiments and seasonings; vinegar and substitutes; yeast and baking powders; stuffed pasta, whether or not cooked; couscous; and protein concentrates. Including turtle eggs and birds' nests.

properties.label: Food preparations, flour, malt extract
properties.description: Food preparations of flour, meal, starch or malt extracts, that either do not contain, or contain less than 50%, cocoa powder. Also, food preparations of milk that either do not contain, or contain less than 10%, cocoa powder.

properties.label: Food wastes
properties.description: Sweetened forage and preparations of a kind used for animal feed, e.g. wine lees, argol.

properties.label: Forage and silage, alfalfa
properties.description: Medicago sativa. A deep-rooted perennial herb used for green fodder, for hay or silage, and for pasture.

properties.label: Forage and silage, clover
properties.description: Trifolium spp.. Various species grown for pasture, green fodder or silage.

properties.label: Forage and silage, grasses nes
properties.description: Including inter alia: bent, redtop, fiorin grass (Agrostis spp.); bluegrass (Poa spp.); Columbus grass (Sorghum almum); fescue (Festuca spp.); Napier, elephant grass (Pennisetum purpureum); orchard grass (Dactylis glomerata); Rhodes grass (Chloris gayana); Sudan grass (Sorghum vulgare var. sudanense); Timothy grass (Phleum pratense). Includes species used for cereal production, if cut green for fodder.

properties.label: Forage and silage, green oilseeds
properties.description: Cut green as grass.

properties.label: Forage and silage, legumes
properties.description: Including inter alia: birdsfoot, trefoil (Lotus corniculatus); lespedeza (Lespedeza spp.); kudzu (Pueraria lobata); sesbania (Sesbania spp.); sainfoin, esparcette (Onobrychis sativa); sulla (Hedysarum coronarium). Includes species of pulses, if harvested for fodder.

properties.label: Forage and silage, maize
properties.description: Maize cut green as grass.

properties.label: Forage and silage, rye grass
properties.description: Italian ryegrass (Lolium multiflorum); English, perennial ryegrass (L. perenne). Quick-growing grasses.

properties.label: Forage and silage, sorghum
properties.description: Usually sweet sorghum, so called for the sweet juice in the stem, which is cut green as grass.

properties.label: Forage products
properties.description: Plants specifically grown for animal feed.

properties.label: Fructose and syrup, other
properties.description: Monosaccharide found in fruits and honey, commercially produced from glucose, sucrose or by hydrolysis of inulin (polysaccharide found mainly in the tubers of the dahlia and the Jerusalem artichoke). Especially suitable for use by diabetics.

properties.label: Fructose chemically pure
properties.description: Or levulose, monosaccharide, present with glucose in sweet fruits and honey.

properties.label: Fruit, citrus nes
properties.description: Including inter alia: bergamot (Citrus bergamia); citron (C. medica var. cedrata); chinotto (C. myrtifolia); kumquat (Fortunella japonica). Some minor varieties of citrus are used primarily in the preparation of perfumes and soft drinks.

properties.label: Fruit, cooked, homogenized preparations
properties.description: Cooked fruit preparations, homogenized for dietetic and infant foods.

properties.label: Fruit, dried nes
properties.description: Dried fruit other than apricots, dates, citrus, figs, grapes, nuts and plums.

properties.label: Fruit, fresh nes
properties.description: Including inter alia: azarole (Crataegus azarolus); babaco (Carica pentagona); elderberry (Sambucus nigra); jujube (Zizyphus jujuba); litchi (nephelium litchi); loquat (Eriobotrya japonica); medlar (Mespilus germanica); pawpaw (Asimina triloba); pomegranate (Punica granatum); prickly pear (Opuntia ficus-indica); rose hips (Rosa spp.); rowanberry (Sorbus aucuparia); service-apple (Sorbus domestica); tamarind (Tamarindus indica); tree-strawberry (Arbutus unedo). Other fresh fruit that are not identified separately because of their minor relevance at the international level. Because of their limited local importance, some countries report fresh fruit under this heading that are classified separately by FAO.

properties.label: Fruit, pome nes
properties.description: Other pome fruit not separately identified. In some countries apples, pears and quinces are reported under this general category.

properties.label: Fruit, prepared nes
properties.description: Fruit, nuts and peel, including frozen, prepared or preserved, jam, paste, marmalade, purâe and cooked fruits, other than those listed separately.

properties.label: Fruit, stone nes
properties.description: Other stone fruit not separately identified. In some countries, apricots, cherries, peaches, nectarines and plums are reported under this general category.

properties.label: Fruit, tropical dried nes
properties.description: Including, whenever possible, dried bananas, plantains and pineapples as well as other unlisted tropical fruits.

properties.label: Fruit, tropical fresh nes
properties.description: Including inter alia: breadfruit (Artocarpus incisa); carambola (Averrhoa carambola); cherimoya, custard apple (Annona spp.); durian (Durio zibethinus); feijoa (Feijoa sellowiana); guava (Psidium guajava); hog plum, mombin (Spondias spp.); jackfruit (Artocarpus integrifolia); longan (nephelium longan); mammee (Mammea americana); mangosteen (Garcinia mangostana); naranjillo (Solanum quitoense); passion fruit (Passiflora edulis); rambutan (nephelium lappaceum); sapote, mamey colorado (Calocarpum mammosum); sapodilla (Achras sapota); star apple, cainito (Chrysophyllum spp.). Other tropical fresh fruit that are not identified separately because of their minor relevance at the international level. In some countries mangoes, avocados, pineapples, dates and papayas are reported under this general category.

properties.label: Fruits, nuts, peel, sugar preserved
properties.description: Fruit, nuts, fruit peel, and other parts of plants preserved with sugar (either drained, glazed or crystallized).

properties.label: Garlic
properties.description: Allium sativum.

properties.label: Geese and guinea fowls
properties.description: Anser spp.. See 1057.

properties.label: Germ, maize
properties.description: The seed embryo that is separated during processing and is valued mainly for its oil.

properties.label: Germ, wheat
properties.description: The seed embryo. Whole or rolled germ is used for oil extraction by solvents. Flaked or ground germ is used in bakers' wares, dietetic preparations, feed supplements and in pharmaceutical preparations.

properties.label: Ghee, butteroil of cow milk
properties.description: Butter from which the water has been removed. Very common in hot countries. Includes also anhydrous butterfat or butter oil.

properties.label: Ginger
properties.description: Zingiber officinale. Rhizome of a perennial herb. It also is used for making beverages. Includes fresh, provisionally preserved or dried, whereas ginger preserved in sugar or syrup is excluded.

properties.label: Glucose and dextrose
properties.description: Glucose is a monosaccharide produced by hydrolysing starch with acids and/or enzymes. Dextrose is chemically pure glucose. Used in the food industry, in brewing, in tobacco fermentation and in pharmaceutical products.

properties.label: Gluten, maize
properties.description: Maize protein is often called gluten, although it lacks the quality characteristics of wheat gluten. It is separated from maize during commercial wet milling and used to enrich animal feeds.

properties.label: Gluten, rice
properties.description: A by-product of the industrial production of starch. Not suitable for food use.

properties.label: Gluten, wheat
properties.description: A by-product of the industrial production of starch, wheat gluten is the preferred cereal gluten for food purposes. Uses include enriching protein in flours for bread, pasta, etc.

properties.label: Goats
properties.description: Capra spp.. See 866. Includes Hircus, Ibex, Nubiana, Pyrenaica, Tibetana, Kashmir and Angora.

properties.label: Gooseberries
properties.description: Ribes grossularia. Trade data may sometimes include black, white or red currants.

properties.label: Grain, mixed
properties.description: A mixture of cereal species that are sown and harvested together. The mixture wheat/rye is known as meslin, but in trade is usually classified with wheat.

properties.label: Grapefruit (inc. pomelos)
properties.description: Citrus maxima; C. grandis; C. paradisi.

properties.label: Grapes
properties.description: Vitis vinifera. Includes both table and wine grapes.

properties.label: Grapes, marc
properties.description: Residues from the pressing of grapes. Used also for distilling.

properties.label: Grapes, must
properties.description: Grape must that has partially fermented, whether or not fermentation has been arrested, as well as unfermented grape must to which alcohol has been added.

properties.label: Grease incl. lanolin wool
properties.description: Extracted from the soapy water in which wool has been scoured, or from greasy wool by meand of solvents. Lanolin is obtained by purifying wool grease. Includes wool grease olein and stearin.

properties.label: Groundnuts, prepared
properties.description: Roasted, salted, flavoured, etc.

properties.label: Groundnuts, shelled
properties.description: Used as direct food and for extracting oil.

properties.label: Groundnuts, with shell
properties.description: Arachis hypogaea. For trade data, groundnuts in shell are converted at 70% and reported on a shelled basis.

properties.label: Gum, arabic
properties.description: Latex exuded by some acacias.

properties.label: Gums, natural
properties.description: Including inter alia: balata (Manilkara bidentata); ceara (Manihot glaziovii); chicle gum (Achras zapota); guayule (Parthenium argentatum); gutta-percha (Palachium gutta); jelutong (Dieva costulana). Extracted from the latex of trees of various species. Although similar to rubber in many ways, natural gums are usually less elastic.

properties.label: Hair, carded/combed
properties.description: Wool and fine or coarse animal hair, carded or combed, including combed wool in fragments.

properties.label: Hair, coarse nes
properties.description: Hair from flanks of equines and bovines, as well as hair from other animals, such as dogs and monkeys. Excludes carded or combed hair.

properties.label: Hair, fine
properties.description: Fine animal hair, mainly from alpaca, llama, vicuÂ¤a, camel and angora rabbit. Excludes carded or combed hair.

properties.label: Hair, goat, coarse
properties.description: Common goat hair. Not carded or combed hair.

properties.label: Hair, goat, fine
properties.description: Hair from cashmere, angora (mohair) and similar goats. Excludes carded or combed hair.

properties.label: Hair, horse
properties.description: Includes hair of the manes and tails of equine and bovine animals and waste therefrom. Hair from flanks included in 1219.

properties.label: Hay (clover, lucerne,etc)
properties.description: Hay from leguminous crops.

properties.label: Hay (unspecified)
properties.description: Hay from unspecified plants.

properties.label: Hay, non-leguminous
properties.description: Hay that is mainly from grasses.

properties.label: Hazelnuts, shelled
properties.description: Around 50% of the weight in shell.

properties.label: Hazelnuts, with shell
properties.description: Corylus avellana. Produced mainly in Mediterranean countries and the United States.

properties.label: Hemp tow waste
properties.description: Cannabis sativa. This plant is cultivated for seed as well as for fibre. The fibre is obtained from the stem of the plant. Trade data include raw, retted, scutched, combed fibre, tow and waste.

properties.label: Hempseed
properties.description: Cannabis sativa. An annual herbaceous that is cultivated for its fibre as well as its oil. In major producing countries oil is extracted from the seeds.

properties.label: Hides and skins nes, fresh
properties.description: See 919. Both adult and young animals. Includes, among others, chamois, antelope, crocodile and snake.

properties.label: Hides, ass, fresh
properties.description: See 919. Both adult and young animals.

properties.label: Hides, buffalo, dry salted
properties.description: See 921.

properties.label: Hides, buffalo, fresh
properties.description: See 919. Both adult and young animals.

properties.label: Hides, buffalo, wet salted
properties.description: See 920.

properties.label: Hides, camel, dry salted
properties.description: See 921.

properties.label: Hides, camel, fresh
properties.description: See 919. Both adult and young animals.

properties.label: Hides, camel, nes
properties.description: See 922.

properties.label: Hides, camel, wet salted
properties.description: See 920.

properties.label: Hides, cattle, dry salted
properties.description: Includes dry and dry-salted, approximately 35% and 55% of green weight, respectively.

properties.label: Hides, cattle, fresh
properties.description: Green hide or skin as removed from the carcass of the animal (adult bovine). Used for production data only.

properties.label: Hides, cattle, nes
properties.description: Limed, pickled or otherwise preserved.

properties.label: Hides, cattle, wet salted
properties.description: Approximately 80-85% of green weight.

properties.label: Hides, horse, dry salted
properties.description: See 921. Includes hides of asses and mules.

properties.label: Hides, horse, fresh
properties.description: See 919. Both adult and young animals.

properties.label: Hides, horse, nes
properties.description: See 922. Includes hides of asses and mules.

properties.label: Hides, horse, wet salted
properties.description: See 920. Includes hides of asses and mules.

properties.label: Hides, mule, fresh
properties.description: See 919. Both adult and young animals.

properties.label: Hides, nes
properties.description: See 922.

properties.label: Hides, nes, dry salted
properties.description: See 921.

properties.label: Hides, wet salted, nes
properties.description: See 920.

properties.label: Honey, natural
properties.description: Honey produced by bees (Apis mellifera) or by other insects.

properties.label: Hops
properties.description: Humulus lupulus. Hop cones, fresh or dried, whether or not ground, powdered or in the form of pellets. Includes lupuline, a yellow resinous powder that covers the hop cones. Mainly used in the brewing industry to give flavour to beer.

properties.label: Horses
properties.description: Equus caballus. See 866.

properties.label: Ice cream and edible ice
properties.description: A product with a milk or cream base to which sweeteners, eggs, etc. have been added.

properties.label: Infant food
properties.description: Preparations for infant consumption, usually containing some non-cereal ingredients.

properties.label: Isoglucose
properties.description: Also known as HFCS (high-fructose corn syrup), HFSS (high-fructose starch syrup), HFGS (high-fructose glucose syrup). Isoglucose is a new type of starch syrup where glucose has been isomerized to fructose by using one or more isomerizing enzymes. Most important of the sweeteners manufactured from maize starch. Widely used in the production of food and soft drinks.

properties.label: Jojoba seed
properties.description: Simmondsia californica (syn. S. chinensis). From the shrub or small tree of the Buxaceae family.

properties.label: Juice, apple, concentrated
properties.description: See 492.

properties.label: Juice, apple, single strength
properties.description: See 491.

properties.label: Juice, citrus, concentrated
properties.description: See 492.

properties.label: Juice, citrus, single strength
properties.description: See 491.

properties.label: Juice, fruit nes
properties.description: See 491.

properties.label: Juice, grape
properties.description: See 491. Includes unfermented grape must.

properties.label: Juice, grapefruit
properties.description: See 491.

properties.label: Juice, grapefruit, concentrated
properties.description: See 492.

properties.label: Juice, lemon, concentrated
properties.description: See 492.

properties.label: Juice, lemon, single strength
properties.description: See 491.

properties.label: Juice, mango
properties.description: See 491.

properties.label: Juice, orange, concentrated
properties.description: Juice that is obtained by a concentration process in which the water is physically removed from the juice until it has not less than 20% of solids by weight. It is then reconstituted with water before consumption. Unfermented, it may or may not be frozen.

properties.label: Juice, orange, single strength
properties.description: Juice is obtained by mechanical extractors, or by pressing, and is then submitted to various processes. Unfermented, it may or may not be frozen. For direct consumption.

properties.label: Juice, pineapple
properties.description: See 491.

properties.label: Juice, pineapple, concentrated
properties.description: See 492. Soluble fruit solids of not less than 27% by weight.

properties.label: Juice, plum, concentrated
properties.description: See 492.

properties.label: Juice, plum, single strength
properties.description: See 491.

properties.label: Juice, tangerine
properties.description: See 491.

properties.label: Juice, tomato
properties.description: Juice is obtained by treating tomatoes with cold or hot water or with steam. The juice then undergoes various processes, such as clarification, homogenization, sterilization, etc.

properties.label: Juice, vegetables nes
properties.description: Juice obtained by pressing, or by treatment with water or with steam, then submitted to various processes. Vegetable juice may contain added salt, spices or flavouring substances.

properties.label: Jute
properties.description: White jute (Corchorus capsularis); red jute, tossa (C. olitorius). Trade data cover raw or processed jute (but not spun), tow and waste, yarn waste and garnetted stock and may include jute-like fibres.

properties.label: Kapok fibre
properties.description: Ceiba pentandra. This plant is cultivated for seed as well as for fibre. Trade data cover only fibres that have been crushed, carded or combed for spinning.

properties.label: Kapok fruit
properties.description: Ceiba pentandra, Bombacaceae. The fruit of kapok contains fibre and seeds, which FAO treats as primary crops.

properties.label: Kapokseed in shell
properties.description: The soft shell is approximately 40-50% of the total weight of the nut.

properties.label: Kapokseed shelled
properties.description: Used for extracting oil.

properties.label: Karite nuts (sheanuts)
properties.description: Butyrospermum parkii. Production data refer only to the nut contained in the fruit although the pulp around the nut is also edible.

properties.label: Kiwi fruit
properties.description: Actinidia chinensis.

properties.label: Kola nuts
properties.description: Kola, cola, Sudan cola nut (Cola nitida; C. vera; C. acuminata). Produced mainly in Africa. Kola nuts, containing 2.4 to 2.6% caffeine, are commonly chewed by the local population. Much used in Europe and America in the production of beverages.

properties.label: Lactose
properties.description: Also known as milk sugar. Produced commercially from whey.

properties.label: Lard
properties.description: Rendered pig fat.

properties.label: Lard stearine oil
properties.description: Obtained by pressing lard or tallow (oleo-oil, tallow oil, tallow stearine).

properties.label: Leather used & waste
properties.description: Parings and other waste of leather, leather dust, powder and flour.

properties.label: Leaves, tops, vines nes
properties.description: Vegetable products that are not specifically grown for animal feed, but are used for that purpose.

properties.label: Leeks, other alliaceous vegetables
properties.description: Leeks (Allium porrum); chives (A. schoenoprasum); other alliac. (Allium varieties except those of 402, 403 and 406).

properties.label: Lemons and limes
properties.description: Lemon (Citrus limon); sour lime (C. aurantifolia); sweet lime (C. limetta).

properties.label: Lentils
properties.description: Lens esculenta; Ervum lens.

properties.label: Lettuce and chicory
properties.description: Lactuca sativa; witloof chicory (Cichorium intybus var. foliosum); endive (C. endivia var. crispa); escarole chicory (C. endivia var. latifolia).

properties.label: Linseed
properties.description: Linum usitatissimum Flaxseed. An annual herbaceous that is cultivated for its fibre as well as its oil.

properties.label: Liver prep.
properties.description: Liver of any animal, excluding fatty livers of code 1060.

properties.label: Lupins
properties.description: Lupinus spp.. Used primarily for feed, though in some parts of Africa and in Latin America some varieties are cultivated for human food.

properties.label: Macaroni
properties.description: Pasta made from semolina, or flour, that is mixed with water and kneaded into a dough. Other ingredients may be included as well. The dough is then shaped into various forms. This heading is limited to macaroni that is not cooked, stuffed or otherwise prepared.

properties.label: Maize
properties.description: Zea mays Corn, Indian corn, mealies. A grain with a high germ content. At the national level, hybrid and ordinary maize should be reported separately owing to widely different yields and uses. Used largely for animal feed and commercial starch production.

properties.label: Maize, green
properties.description: Zea mays, particularly var. saccharata. Maize harvested green for food. Saccharata variety is commonly known as sweet corn.

properties.label: Malt
properties.description: A grain - usually barley - that has been germinated through a soaking process and then dried. Malt is used in brewing and distilling, and as a nutrient additive. Includes whole, ground, flour, and roasted malt, but excludes extracts and preparations.

properties.label: Malt extract
properties.description: A concentrated solution from water-macerated malt, which is used in infant and dietetic foods and in bread baking.

properties.label: Maltose chemically pure
properties.description: Produced industrially from starch by hydrolysis with malt diastase. Used in the brewing industry.

properties.label: Mango pulp
properties.description: Fruit pulp prepared in water, syrup, etc.

properties.label: Mangoes, mangosteens, guavas
properties.description: Mangifera indica. Trade figures may include dried mangoes, guavas and mangosteens, including both fresh and dried.

properties.label: Manila fibre (abaca)
properties.description: Musa textilis. The fibre is obtained from stalks of certain banana trees. For trade coverage see 789.

properties.label: Maple sugar and syrups
properties.description: Maple syrup is produced by atmospheric boiling of maple sap in an open-pan evaporator. Continuing the evaporation process until the syrup crystalizes yields maple sugar.

properties.label: Margarine, liquid
properties.description: See commodity code 1242. Fat content varies from 30 to 70%.

properties.label: Margarine, short
properties.description: Margarine is made principally from one or more hydrogenated vegetable or animal fats or oils in which is dispersed an aqueous potion containing milk products, salt, flavouring agents and other additives. Shortening is a product similar to margarine, but with a higher animal fat content. Shortening and compound fats are used primarily for baking and frying. The fat content of margarine and shortening varies from 70 to 90%.

properties.label: MatÃ©
properties.description: Ilex paraguayensis. The dried leaves of certain shrubs of the holly family which grow in South America. Prepared in a way similar to tea.

properties.label: Meal, blood
properties.description: Flours, meals and pellets obtained through dehydration of blood. Used for feed.

properties.label: Meal, meat
properties.description: Flours, meals and pellets of meat and offal (including of marine mammals); greaves and tankage. Used for feed.

items.label: Meat live weight, buffalo live weight

properties.membername: Meat live weight, buffalo live weight
properties.label: Meat live weight, buffalo live weight
Meat, ass
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Meat, beef and veal sausages
properties.description: Preparations of meat or offal, whether chopped, minced or of blood. They may be raw, cooked or smoked and contain other ingredients, andare then enclosed in natural or artificial casings.

properties.label: Meat, beef, dried, salted, smoked
properties.description: Meat of bovine animals, whether salted, in brine, dried or smoked. Includes edible flours and meals.

properties.label: Meat, beef, preparations
properties.description: Meat and offal (o/t liver) that are boiled, steamed, grilled, fried,roasted or otherwise cooked. Includes prepared meals that contain morethan 20% of meat and offal by weight.

properties.label: Meat, bird nes
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Meat, buffalo
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen, with bone in or boneless.

properties.label: Meat, camel
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Meat, cattle
properties.description: Meat of bovine animals, fresh, chilled or frozen, with bone in. Commontrade names are beef and veal.

properties.label: Meat, cattle, boneless (beef & veal)
properties.description: Boneless meat of bovine animals, whether fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Meat, chicken
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen. May include all types of poultry meat ifnational statistics do not report separate data.

properties.label: Meat, chicken, canned
properties.description: Includes meat and offals of poultry.

properties.label: Meat, dried nes
properties.description: Meat, except of bovines and pigs, salted, in brine or smoked.

properties.label: Meat, duck
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Meat, extracts
properties.description: Extracts obtained by boiling meat under pressure and concentrating theresulting liquid after the fat has been removed. Includes juicesobtained by pressing raw meat. Whenever possible trade data excludefish extracts.

properties.label: Meat, game
properties.description: Meat and offals of wild animals, whether fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Meat, goat
properties.description: Meat of goats and kids, whether fresh, chilled or frozen, with bone inor boneless.

properties.label: Meat, goose and guinea fowl
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Meat, homogenized preparations
properties.description: Preparations used in infant or dietetic food.

properties.label: Meat, horse
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Meat, mule
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Meat, nes
properties.description: Including frog legs, marine mammals, etc. Some countries includeunder this heading meats that are listed above, but which are notreported separately. Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Meat, nes, preparations
properties.description: Excludes poultry, swine or bovine meat preparations.

properties.label: Meat, other camelids
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Meat, other rodents
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Meat, pig
properties.description: Meat, with the bone in, of domestic or wild pigs (e.g. wild boars),whether fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Meat, pig sausages
properties.description: See 874.

properties.label: Meat, pig, preparations
properties.description: See 875.

properties.label: Meat, pork
properties.description: Pig meat, excluding butcher fat and bones.

properties.label: Meat, rabbit
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen. May include hare meat.

properties.label: Meat, sheep
properties.description: Meat of sheep and lamb, whether fresh, chilled or frozen, with bone inor boneless.

properties.label: Meat, turkey
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Melons, other (inc.cantaloupes)
properties.description: Cucumis melo;.

properties.label: Melonseed
properties.description: Cucumis melo. Includes seeds of other Cucurbitaceae.

items.label: Milk, products of natural constituents nes

properties.membername: Milk, products of natural constituents nes
properties.label: Milk, products of natural constituents nes
Milk, reconstituted
properties.description: Obtained by adding water, fat, etc. to milk powder.

properties.label: Milk, skimmed condensed
properties.description: Same as 889, but applied to skim milk.

properties.label: Milk, skimmed cow
properties.description: Milk from which most of the fat has been removed.

properties.label: Milk, skimmed dried
properties.description: Same as 897, but from skim milk. Normally does not exceed 1.5% fat content.

properties.label: Milk, skimmed evaporated
properties.description: Same as 894, but applied to skim milk.

properties.label: Milk, standardized
properties.description: Milk in which the fat content is adjusted to a predetermined value without altering any other constituents.

properties.label: Milk, whole condensed
properties.description: Milk and cream from which water has been partly removed after heat-treating and concentrating. Normally sucrose is added to give the product stability and bacteriological safety.

properties.label: Milk, whole dried
properties.description: Milk and cream from which water has been completely removed by various methods. In form of powder, granules or other solid forms. May contain added sugar or other sweeteners.

properties.label: Milk, whole evaporated
properties.description: Milk and cream from which the water has been partly removed and which has been heat- treated to render it bacteriologically safe and stable.

properties.label: Milk, whole fresh buffalo
properties.description: See 882 and derived products.

properties.label: Milk, whole fresh camel
properties.description: See 882.

properties.label: Milk, whole fresh cow
properties.description: Production data refer to raw milk containing all its constituents. Trade data normally cover milk from any animal, and refer to milk that is not concentrated, pasteurized, sterilized or other-wise preserved, homogenized or peptonized.

properties.label: Milk, whole fresh goat
properties.description: See 882 and derived products.

properties.label: Milk, whole fresh sheep
properties.description: See 882 and derived products.

properties.label: Millet
properties.description: Including inter alia: barnyard or Japanese millet (Echinocloa frumentacea); ragi, finger or African millet (Eleusine coracana); teff (Eragrostis abyssinica); common, golden or proso millet (Panicum miliaceum); koda or ditch millet (Paspalum scrobiculatum); pearl or cattail millet (Pennisetum glaucum); foxtail millet (Setaria italica). Small-grained cereals that include a large number of different botanical species. Originated by the domestication of wild African grasses in the Nile valley and the Sahel zone, millets were subsequently taken to China and India. These cereals tolerate arid conditions and possess a small, highly nutritious grain that stores well. Used locally, both as a food and as a livestock feed. In all areas where they are cultivated, millets are used in traditional beer brewing. Also used as a feed for birds.

properties.label: Molasses
properties.description: A by-product of the extraction or refining of beet or cane sugar or of the production of fructose from maize. Used for feed, food, industrial alcohol, alcoholic beverages and ethanol.

properties.label: Mules
properties.description: Includes hinnies. Mules are offspring of a male ass and a female horse (mare); a hinny is the offspring of a female ass and a male horse (stallion). Both are sterile. See 866.

properties.label: Mushrooms and truffles
properties.description: Including inter alia: Boletus edulis; Agaricus campestris; Morchella spp. and Tuber magnatum. Cultivated or spontaneous. Includes truffles.

properties.label: Mushrooms, canned
properties.description: Mushrooms and truffles, prepared or preserved o/t by vinegar or acetic acid; either whole, in pieces, or homogenized.

properties.label: Mushrooms, dried
properties.description: Mushrooms and truffles, whether dried, dehydrated, evaporated or freeze-dried.

properties.label: Mustard seed
properties.description: White mustard (Brassica alba; B. hirta; Sinapis alba); black mustard (Brassica nigra; Sinapis nigra). In addition to the oil extracted from them, white mustard seeds, may be processed into flour for food use. Black mustard seeds also yield oil and are processed into flour that is used mainly in pharmaceutical products.

properties.label: Nutmeg, mace and cardamoms
properties.description: Nutmeg, mace (Myristica fragrans); cluster cardamon (Elettaria cardamomum); other cardamons (Aframomum angustifolium; A. hambury; Amomun aromaticum; A. cardamomum); Malaguetta pepper, grains of paradise (Aframomum melegueta). Nutmeg is the inner brown kernel of the fruit of the nutmeg tree. Mace is the net-like membrane between the outer shell and the kernel. Cardamon seeds are enclosed in the capsule produced by perennial herbs of the Zingiberaceae family.

properties.label: Nuts, nes
properties.description: Including inter alia: pecan nut (Carya illinoensis); butter or swarri nut (Caryocar nuciferum); pili nut, Java almond, Chinese olives (Canarium spp.); paradise or sapucaia nut (Lecythis zabucajo); Queensland, macadamia nut (Macadamia ternifolia); pignolia nut (Pinus pinea). Other nuts that are not identified separately because of their minor relevance at the international level. Because of their limited local importance, some countries report nuts under this heading that are classified individually by FAO.

properties.label: Nuts, prepared (exc. groundnuts)
properties.description: Mainly roasted, whether or not containing vegetable oils, salt, flavours, spices or other additives. Excludes prepared groundnuts, except when mixed with other nuts.

properties.label: Oats
properties.description: Avena spp., mainly Avena sativa. A plant with open, spreading panicle-bearing large spikelets. Used primarily in breakfast foods. Makes excellent fodder for horses.

properties.label: Oats rolled
properties.description: Obtained by crushing or rolling the whole or broken grain; includes grains flaked, hulled or otherwise worked for human consumption.

properties.label: Offals, edible, buffaloes
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Offals, edible, camels
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Offals, edible, cattle
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Offals, edible, goats
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Offals, horses
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Offals, liver chicken
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Offals, liver duck
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen, salted or in brine.

properties.label: Offals, liver geese
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen, salted or in brine.

properties.label: Offals, nes
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Offals, pigs, edible
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Offals, sheep,edible
properties.description: Fresh, chilled or frozen.

properties.label: Oil, boiled etc
properties.description: Also includes oxidized and sulphurized oils. Animal and vegetable fats and oils whose chemical structure has been modified to improve viscosity, drying ability or other properties.

properties.label: Oil, castor beans
properties.description: Obtained by pressure or by solvent. Uses include mainly industrial ones, in pharmaceuticals and cosmetics.

properties.label: Oil, citronella
properties.description: Essential oil extracted from Cymbopogon nardus.

properties.label: Oil, coconut (copra)
properties.description: Obtained by pressure from copra and by solvent from the residues of pressure extraction. Has both food and industrial uses.

properties.label: Oil, cottonseed
properties.description: Obtained first by pressure extraction from the kernels of cotton seeds. The residue from this process is then exposed to a solvent. Used mainly as a food.

properties.label: Oil, essential nes
properties.description: Extracted from many plants and used mainly in the perfumery, food and other industries.

properties.label: Oil, groundnut
properties.description: Obtained by pressure or solvent extraction. Used mainly for food.

properties.label: Oil, hempseed
properties.description: Obtained either by pressure extraction or by solvent. Used mainly in non-food items.

properties.label: Oil, hydrogenated
properties.description: Animal and vegetable fats and oils that have been hydrogenated to raise their melting point and increase their consistency by transforming unsaturated glycerides into saturated glycerides.

properties.label: Oil, jojoba
properties.description: Obtained by cold pressure. Its peculiar chemical properties make it the only vegetable oil in nature having the same characteristics as spermaceti. Below 15Ã¸C it solidifies and assumes the characteristics of wax. It is used as a lubricant, in cosmetics and in pharmaceuticals, and is considered a product with good growth prospects.

properties.label: Oil, kapok
properties.description: Obtained from shelled seeds by pressure. Used for food and soap.

properties.label: Oil, linseed
properties.description: Obtained by pressure extraction. Used mainly in non-food items.

properties.label: Oil, maize
properties.description: Extracted from germ by pressure or by solvents.

properties.label: Oil, mustard
properties.description: Obtained by dry pressure extraction. Has both food and industrial uses.

properties.label: Oil, olive residues
properties.description: Oil extracted from olive residues with solvents.

properties.label: Oil, olive, virgin
properties.description: Obtained from olives by mechanical or other physical means. Olive oil is the only vegetable oil that can be consumed without refining.

properties.label: Oil, palm
properties.description: Obtained from the mesocarp of the fruit of the oil palm by pressure, and also by solvent from the residues of the pressure extraction.

properties.label: Oil, palm fruit
properties.description: Elaeis guineensis. The oil palm produces bunches containing a large number of fruits with the fleshy mesocarp enclosing a kernel that is covered by a very hard shell. FAO considers palm oil (coming from the pulp) and palm kernels to be primary products. The oil extraction rate from a bunch varies from 17 to 27% for palm oil, and from 4 to 10% for palm kernels.

properties.label: Oil, palm kernel
properties.description: Obtained from the kernel of the nut of the fruits of the oil palm by pressure in two or three stages at different temperatures. Including oil of babassu kernels.

properties.label: Oil, poppy
properties.description: Obtained by pressure extraction. Has both food and industrial uses.

properties.label: Oil, rapeseed
properties.description: Obtained by pressure extraction for food use. Oil recovered with solvent from the residues of the pressure extraction is used for industrial purposes. Canola oil is produced from new varieties of rapeseed.

properties.label: Oil, rice bran
properties.description: Extracted from bran by pressure or, more frequently, by solvents.

properties.label: Oil, safflower
properties.description: Obtained either by pressure or by solvent. Has both food and industrial uses.

properties.label: Oil, sesame
properties.description: Obtained by pressure extraction in two or three stages at different temperatures. Sometimes the oil is also extracted by solvent from the residue of the pressure extraction. Used mainly for food.

properties.label: Oil, soybean
properties.description: Obtained by solvent extraction from the beans. Used mainly for food.

properties.label: Oil, stillingia
properties.description: Obtained by solvent from the seeds of Stillingia sebifera. Used as a drying agent in paints and varnishes.

properties.label: Oil, sunflower
properties.description: Obtained by pressure extraction. Mainly for food use.

properties.label: Oil, tung nuts
properties.description: Obtained by pressure and used exclusively for industrial purposes. The resulting cake contains a toxic protein and thus cannot be used for feed.

properties.label: Oil, vegetable origin nes
properties.description: Includes, inter alia, myrtle wax and Japan wax.

properties.label: Oils, fats of animal nes
properties.description: Animal oils and fats obtained from other animal species and oils and fats recovered from guts, feet, sweepings, hide trimmings, etc.

properties.label: Oilseeds nes
properties.description: Includes inter alia: beech nut (Fagus sylvatica);(Aleurites moluccana);(Carapa guineensis);(Croton tiglium);(Bassia latifolia);(Guizotia abyssinica);(Licania rigida);(Perilla frutescens);(Jatropha curcas);(Shorea robusta);(Pongamia glabra);(Astrocaryum spp.). Other oilseeds, oleaginous fruits and nuts that are not identified separately because of their minor relevance at the international level. Because of their limited local importance, some countries report commodities under this heading that are classified individually by FAO. Also included under this code are tea seeds, grape pips and tomato seeds from which oil is extracted.

properties.label: Okra
properties.description: Abelmoschus esculentus; Hibiscus esculentus. Also called gombo.

properties.label: Olive residues
properties.description: Residues make up about 40% of the olives crushed for oil, but account for about 5% of the oil.

properties.label: Olives
properties.description: Olea europaea. Includes table olives and olives for oil.

properties.label: Olives preserved
properties.description: Treated with SO2, brine, water, or otherwise prepared or preserved.

properties.label: Onions, dry
properties.description: Allium cepa. Includes onions at a mature stage, but not dehydrated onions.

properties.label: Onions, shallots, green
properties.description: Shallots (Allium ascalonicum); onions (A. cepa); welsh onions (A. fistulosum). Young onions pulled before the bulb has enlarged; used especially in salads. Includes onion sets.

properties.label: Oranges
properties.description: Common, sweet orange (Citrus sinensis); bitter orange (C. aurantium). Bitter oranges are used primarily in the preparation of marmalade.

properties.label: Palm kernels
properties.description: Seeds of the oil palm. Babassu kernels (Orbignya speciosa) are often reported as palm kernels.

properties.label: Papayas
properties.description: Carica papaya.

properties.label: Pastry
properties.description: All baked products excluding those listed under bread. Pastry products may contain ingredients other than wheat flour, such as milk, eggs, sugar, honey, starch, fats, fruit, seeds, etc.

properties.label: Peaches and nectarines
properties.description: Prunus persica; Amygdalus persica; Persica laevis.

properties.label: Peanut butter
properties.description: Obtained by grinding roasted peanuts. In addition to fat, at 40-46%, peanut butter contains all other components of the nuts.

properties.label: Pears
properties.description: Pyrus communis.

properties.label: Peas, dry
properties.description: Garden pea (Pisum sativum); field pea (P. arvense).

properties.label: Peas, green
properties.description: Pisum sativum. Mostly for shelling, but including edible- podded peas or sugar peas.

properties.label: Pepper (piper spp.)
properties.description: Black, white pepper (Piper nigrum); long pepper (P. longum). Perennial climbing vines. Includes whole, crushed or ground berries. Black pepper is produced from partially ripe berries, while white pepper is from fully ripe berries which have had the outer hull removed.

properties.label: Peppermint
properties.description: Mentha spp.: M. piperita. Leaves and flowers are used in the perfumery, food and other industries.

properties.label: Persimmons
properties.description: Diospyros kaki: D. virginiana.

properties.label: Pet food
